                      "fill": "$neutral-100",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "A beloved English Christmas carol dating to the 13th century, &quot;The First Noel&quot; follows a AAB musical form across six stanzas. The melody, rooted in the Dorian mode, presents a pastoral narrative of the Nativity. This SATB arrangement preserves the hymn-like character while distributing the cantus firmus across soprano and tenor voices, with inner voices providing harmonic support through subdominant and dominant progressions.",
